53RenderGrid::RenderGrid(Element& element, RenderStyle&& style)
54 : RenderBlock(element, WTFMove(style), 0)
55 , m_grid(*this)
56 , m_trackSizingAlgorithm(this, m_grid)
57{
58 // All of our children must be block level.
59 setChildrenInline(false);
60
61 InspectorInstrumentation::nodeLayoutContextChanged(element, this);
62}
63
64RenderGrid::~RenderGrid()
65{
66 InspectorInstrumentation::nodeLayoutContextChanged(element(), nullptr);
67}

69StyleSelfAlignmentData RenderGrid::selfAlignmentForChild(GridAxis axis, const RenderBox& child, const RenderStyle* gridStyle) const
70{
71 return axis == GridRowAxis ? justifySelfForChild(child, gridStyle) : alignSelfForChild(child, gridStyle);
72}
73
74bool RenderGrid::selfAlignmentChangedToStretch(GridAxis axis, const RenderStyle& oldStyle, const RenderStyle& newStyle, const RenderBox& child) const
75{
76 return selfAlignmentForChild(axis, child, &oldStyle).position() != ItemPosition::Stretch
77 && selfAlignmentForChild(axis, child, &newStyle).position() == ItemPosition::Stretch;
78}
79
80bool RenderGrid::selfAlignmentChangedFromStretch(GridAxis axis, const RenderStyle& oldStyle, const RenderStyle& newStyle, const RenderBox& child) const
81{
82 return selfAlignmentForChild(axis, child, &oldStyle).position() == ItemPosition::Stretch
83 && selfAlignmentForChild(axis, child, &newStyle).position() != ItemPosition::Stretch;
84}
85
86void RenderGrid::styleDidChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
87{
88 RenderBlock::styleDidChange(diff, oldStyle);
89 if (!oldStyle || diff != StyleDifference::Layout)
90 return;
91
92 const RenderStyle& newStyle = this->style();
93 if (oldStyle->resolvedAlignItems(selfAlignmentNormalBehavior(this)).position() == ItemPosition::Stretch) {
94 // Style changes on the grid container implying stretching (to-stretch) or
95 // shrinking (from-stretch) require the affected items to be laid out again.
96 // These logic only applies to 'stretch' since the rest of the alignment
97 // values don't change the size of the box.
98 // In any case, the items' overrideSize will be cleared and recomputed (if
99 // necessary) as part of the Grid layout logic, triggered by this style
100 // change.
101 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<RenderBox>(*this)) {
102 if (child.isOutOfFlowPositioned())
103 continue;
104 if (selfAlignmentChangedToStretch(GridRowAxis, *oldStyle, newStyle, child)
105 || selfAlignmentChangedFromStretch(GridRowAxis, *oldStyle, newStyle, child)
106 || selfAlignmentChangedToStretch(GridColumnAxis, *oldStyle, newStyle, child)
107 || selfAlignmentChangedFromStretch(GridColumnAxis, *oldStyle, newStyle, child)) {
108 child.setNeedsLayout();
109 }
110 }
111 }
112
113 if (explicitGridDidResize(*oldStyle) || namedGridLinesDefinitionDidChange(*oldStyle) || oldStyle->gridAutoFlow() != style().gridAutoFlow()
114 || (style().gridAutoRepeatColumns().size() || style().gridAutoRepeatRows().size()))
115 dirtyGrid();
116}
117
118bool RenderGrid::explicitGridDidResize(const RenderStyle& oldStyle) const
119{
120 return oldStyle.gridColumns().size() != style().gridColumns().size()
121 || oldStyle.gridRows().size() != style().gridRows().size()
122 || oldStyle.namedGridAreaColumnCount() != style().namedGridAreaColumnCount()
123 || oldStyle.namedGridAreaRowCount() != style().namedGridAreaRowCount()
124 || oldStyle.gridAutoRepeatColumns().size() != style().gridAutoRepeatColumns().size()
125 || oldStyle.gridAutoRepeatRows().size() != style().gridAutoRepeatRows().size();
126}
127
128bool RenderGrid::namedGridLinesDefinitionDidChange(const RenderStyle& oldStyle) const
129{
130 return oldStyle.namedGridRowLines() != style().namedGridRowLines()
131 || oldStyle.namedGridColumnLines() != style().namedGridColumnLines();
132}

134// This method optimizes the gutters computation by skiping the available size
135// call if gaps are fixed size (it's only needed for percentages).
136std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderGrid::availableSpaceForGutters(GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
137{
138 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
139 const GapLength& gapLength = isRowAxis ? style().columnGap() : style().rowGap();
140 if (gapLength.isNormal() || !gapLength.length().isPercentOrCalculated())
141 return std::nullopt;
142
143 return isRowAxis ? availableLogicalWidth() : contentLogicalHeight();
144}

146void RenderGrid::computeTrackSizesForDefiniteSize(GridTrackSizingDirection direction, LayoutUnit availableSpace)
147{
148 m_trackSizingAlgorithm.setup(direction, numTracks(direction, m_grid), TrackSizing, availableSpace);
149 m_trackSizingAlgorithm.run();
150
151 ASSERT(m_trackSizingAlgorithm.tracksAreWiderThanMinTrackBreadth());
152}
153
154void RenderGrid::repeatTracksSizingIfNeeded(LayoutUnit availableSpaceForColumns, LayoutUnit availableSpaceForRows)
155{
156 // In orthogonal flow cases column track's size is determined by using the computed
157 // row track's size, which it was estimated during the first cycle of the sizing
158 // algorithm. Hence we need to repeat computeUsedBreadthOfGridTracks for both,
159 // columns and rows, to determine the final values.
160 // TODO (lajava): orthogonal flows is just one of the cases which may require
161 // a new cycle of the sizing algorithm; there may be more. In addition, not all the
162 // cases with orthogonal flows require this extra cycle; we need a more specific
163 // condition to detect whether child's min-content contribution has changed or not.
164 if (m_hasAnyOrthogonalItem || m_trackSizingAlgorithm.hasAnyPercentSizedRowsIndefiniteHeight()) {
165 computeTrackSizesForDefiniteSize(ForColumns, availableSpaceForColumns);
166 computeContentPositionAndDistributionOffset(ForColumns, m_trackSizingAlgorithm.freeSpace(ForColumns).value(), nonCollapsedTracks(ForColumns));
167 computeTrackSizesForDefiniteSize(ForRows, availableSpaceForRows);
168 computeContentPositionAndDistributionOffset(ForRows, m_trackSizingAlgorithm.freeSpace(ForRows).value(), nonCollapsedTracks(ForRows));
169 }
170}

172bool RenderGrid::canPerformSimplifiedLayout() const
173{
174 // We cannot perform a simplified layout if we need to position the items and we have some
175 // positioned items to be laid out.
176 if (m_grid.needsItemsPlacement() && posChildNeedsLayout())
177 return false;
178
179 return RenderBlock::canPerformSimplifiedLayout();
180}
181
182void RenderGrid::layoutBlock(bool relayoutChildren, LayoutUnit)
183{
184 ASSERT(needsLayout());
185
186 if (!relayoutChildren && simplifiedLayout())
187 return;
188
189 LayoutRepainter repainter(*this, checkForRepaintDuringLayout());
190 {
191 LayoutStateMaintainer statePusher(*this, locationOffset(), hasTransform() || hasReflection() || style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode());
192
193 preparePaginationBeforeBlockLayout(relayoutChildren);
194 beginUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
195
196 LayoutSize previousSize = size();
197 // FIXME: We should use RenderBlock::hasDefiniteLogicalHeight() only but it does not work for positioned stuff.
198 // FIXME: Consider caching the hasDefiniteLogicalHeight value throughout the layout.
199 // FIXME: We might need to cache the hasDefiniteLogicalHeight if the call of RenderBlock::hasDefiniteLogicalHeight() causes a relevant performance regression.
200 bool hasDefiniteLogicalHeight = RenderBlock::hasDefiniteLogicalHeight() || hasOverridingLogicalHeight() || computeContentLogicalHeight(MainOrPreferredSize, style().logicalHeight(), std::nullopt);
201 m_hasAnyOrthogonalItem = false;
202 for (auto* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
203 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
204 continue;
205 // Grid's layout logic controls the grid item's override height, hence we need to
206 // clear any override height set previously, so it doesn't interfere in current layout
207 // execution. Grid never uses the override width, that's why we don't need to clear it.
208 child->clearOverridingLogicalHeight();
209
210 // We may need to repeat the track sizing in case of any grid item was orthogonal.
211 if (GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, *child))
212 m_hasAnyOrthogonalItem = true;
213
214 // We keep a cache of items with baseline as alignment values so
215 // that we only compute the baseline shims for such items. This
216 // cache is needed for performance related reasons due to the
217 // cost of evaluating the item's participation in a baseline
218 // context during the track sizing algorithm.
219 if (isBaselineAlignmentForChild(*child, GridColumnAxis))
220 m_trackSizingAlgorithm.cacheBaselineAlignedItem(*child, GridColumnAxis);
221 if (isBaselineAlignmentForChild(*child, GridRowAxis))
222 m_trackSizingAlgorithm.cacheBaselineAlignedItem(*child, GridRowAxis);
223 }
224 m_baselineItemsCached = true;
225 resetLogicalHeightBeforeLayoutIfNeeded();
226 updateLogicalWidth();
227
228 // Fieldsets need to find their legend and position it inside the border of the object.
229 // The legend then gets skipped during normal layout. The same is true for ruby text.
230 // It doesn't get included in the normal layout process but is instead skipped.
231 layoutExcludedChildren(relayoutChildren);
232
233 LayoutUnit availableSpaceForColumns = availableLogicalWidth();
234 placeItemsOnGrid(m_trackSizingAlgorithm, availableSpaceForColumns);
235
236 m_trackSizingAlgorithm.setAvailableSpace(ForColumns, availableSpaceForColumns);
237 performGridItemsPreLayout(m_trackSizingAlgorithm);
238
239 // 1- First, the track sizing algorithm is used to resolve the sizes of the
240 // grid columns.
241 // At this point the logical width is always definite as the above call to
242 // updateLogicalWidth() properly resolves intrinsic sizes. We cannot do the
243 // same for heights though because many code paths inside
244 // updateLogicalHeight() require a previous call to setLogicalHeight() to
245 // resolve heights properly (like for positioned items for example).
246 computeTrackSizesForDefiniteSize(ForColumns, availableSpaceForColumns);
247
248 // 1.5- Compute Content Distribution offsets for column tracks
249 computeContentPositionAndDistributionOffset(ForColumns, m_trackSizingAlgorithm.freeSpace(ForColumns).value(), nonCollapsedTracks(ForColumns));
250
251 // 2- Next, the track sizing algorithm resolves the sizes of the grid rows,
252 // using the grid column sizes calculated in the previous step.
253 bool shouldRecomputeHeight = false;
254 if (!hasDefiniteLogicalHeight) {
255 computeTrackSizesForIndefiniteSize(m_trackSizingAlgorithm, ForRows);
256 if (shouldApplySizeContainment(*this))
257 shouldRecomputeHeight = true;
258 } else
259 computeTrackSizesForDefiniteSize(ForRows, availableLogicalHeight(ExcludeMarginBorderPadding));
260 LayoutUnit trackBasedLogicalHeight = m_trackSizingAlgorithm.computeTrackBasedSize() + borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() + scrollbarLogicalHeight();
261 if (shouldRecomputeHeight)
262 computeTrackSizesForDefiniteSize(ForRows, trackBasedLogicalHeight);
263
264 setLogicalHeight(trackBasedLogicalHeight);
265
266 LayoutUnit oldClientAfterEdge = clientLogicalBottom();
267 updateLogicalHeight();
268
269 // Once grid's indefinite height is resolved, we can compute the
270 // available free space for Content Alignment.
271 if (!hasDefiniteLogicalHeight)
272 m_trackSizingAlgorithm.setFreeSpace(ForRows, logicalHeight() - trackBasedLogicalHeight);
273
274 // 2.5- Compute Content Distribution offsets for rows tracks
275 computeContentPositionAndDistributionOffset(ForRows, m_trackSizingAlgorithm.freeSpace(ForRows).value(), nonCollapsedTracks(ForRows));
276
277 // 3- If the min-content contribution of any grid items have changed based on the row
278 // sizes calculated in step 2, steps 1 and 2 are repeated with the new min-content
279 // contribution (once only).
280 repeatTracksSizingIfNeeded(availableSpaceForColumns, contentLogicalHeight());
281
282 // Grid container should have the minimum height of a line if it's editable. That does not affect track sizing though.
283 if (hasLineIfEmpty()) {
284 LayoutUnit minHeightForEmptyLine = borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight()
285 + lineHeight(true, isHorizontalWritingMode() ? HorizontalLine : VerticalLine, PositionOfInteriorLineBoxes)
286 + scrollbarLogicalHeight();
287 setLogicalHeight(std::max(logicalHeight(), minHeightForEmptyLine));
288 }
289
290 layoutGridItems();
291 m_trackSizingAlgorithm.reset();
292
293 endAndCommitUpdateScrollInfoAfterLayoutTransaction();
294
295 if (size() != previousSize)
296 relayoutChildren = true;
297
298 m_outOfFlowItemColumn.clear();
299 m_outOfFlowItemRow.clear();
300
301 layoutPositionedObjects(relayoutChildren || isDocumentElementRenderer());
302
303 computeOverflow(oldClientAfterEdge);
304 }
305
306 updateLayerTransform();
307
308 // Update our scroll information if we're overflow:auto/scroll/hidden now that we know if
309 // we overflow or not.
310 updateScrollInfoAfterLayout();
311
312 repainter.repaintAfterLayout();
313
314 clearNeedsLayout();
315
316 m_trackSizingAlgorithm.clearBaselineItemsCache();
317 m_baselineItemsCached = false;
318}

320LayoutUnit RenderGrid::gridGap(GridTrackSizingDirection direction, std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableSize) const
321{
322 ASSERT(!availableSize || *availableSize >= 0);
323 const GapLength& gapLength = direction == ForColumns? style().columnGap() : style().rowGap();
324 if (gapLength.isNormal())
325 return 0_lu;
326
327 return valueForLength(gapLength.length(), availableSize.value_or(0));
328}
329
330LayoutUnit RenderGrid::gridGap(GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
331{
332 return gridGap(direction, availableSpaceForGutters(direction));
333}
334
335LayoutUnit RenderGrid::gridItemOffset(GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
336{
337 return direction == ForRows ? m_offsetBetweenRows.distributionOffset : m_offsetBetweenColumns.distributionOffset;
338}
339
340LayoutUnit RenderGrid::guttersSize(const Grid& grid, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, unsigned startLine, unsigned span, std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableSize) const
341{
342 if (span <= 1)
343 return { };
344
345 LayoutUnit gap = gridGap(direction, availableSize);
346
347 // Fast path, no collapsing tracks.
348 if (!grid.hasAutoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction))
349 return gap * (span - 1);
350
351 // If there are collapsing tracks we need to be sure that gutters are properly collapsed. Apart
352 // from that, if we have a collapsed track in the edges of the span we're considering, we need
353 // to move forward (or backwards) in order to know whether the collapsed tracks reach the end of
354 // the grid (so the gap becomes 0) or there is a non empty track before that.
355
356 LayoutUnit gapAccumulator;
357 unsigned endLine = startLine + span;
358
359 for (unsigned line = startLine; line < endLine - 1; ++line) {
360 if (!grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, line))
361 gapAccumulator += gap;
362 }
363
364 // The above loop adds one extra gap for trailing collapsed tracks.
365 if (gapAccumulator && grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, endLine - 1)) {
366 ASSERT(gapAccumulator >= gap);
367 gapAccumulator -= gap;
368 }
369
370 // If the startLine is the start line of a collapsed track we need to go backwards till we reach
371 // a non collapsed track. If we find a non collapsed track we need to add that gap.
372 size_t nonEmptyTracksBeforeStartLine = 0;
373 if (startLine && grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, startLine)) {
374 nonEmptyTracksBeforeStartLine = startLine;
375 auto begin = grid.autoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction)->begin();
376 for (auto it = begin; *it != startLine; ++it) {
377 ASSERT(nonEmptyTracksBeforeStartLine);
378 --nonEmptyTracksBeforeStartLine;
379 }
380 if (nonEmptyTracksBeforeStartLine)
381 gapAccumulator += gap;
382 }
383
384 // If the endLine is the end line of a collapsed track we need to go forward till we reach a non
385 // collapsed track. If we find a non collapsed track we need to add that gap.
386 if (grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, endLine - 1)) {
387 unsigned nonEmptyTracksAfterEndLine = grid.numTracks(direction) - endLine;
388 auto currentEmptyTrack = grid.autoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction)->find(endLine - 1);
389 auto endEmptyTrack = grid.autoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction)->end();
390 // HashSet iterators do not implement operator- so we have to manually iterate to know the number of remaining empty tracks.
391 for (auto it = ++currentEmptyTrack; it != endEmptyTrack; ++it) {
392 ASSERT(nonEmptyTracksAfterEndLine >= 1);
393 --nonEmptyTracksAfterEndLine;
394 }
395 if (nonEmptyTracksAfterEndLine) {
396 // We shouldn't count the gap twice if the span starts and ends in a collapsed track bewtween two non-empty tracks.
397 if (!nonEmptyTracksBeforeStartLine)
398 gapAccumulator += gap;
399 } else if (nonEmptyTracksBeforeStartLine) {
400 // We shouldn't count the gap if the the span starts and ends in a collapsed but there isn't non-empty tracks afterwards (it's at the end of the grid).
401 gapAccumulator -= gap;
402 }
403 }
404
405 return gapAccumulator;
406}

408void RenderGrid::computeIntrinsicLogicalWidths(LayoutUnit& minLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxLogicalWidth) const
409{
410 LayoutUnit childMinWidth;
411 LayoutUnit childMaxWidth;
412 bool hadExcludedChildren = computePreferredWidthsForExcludedChildren(childMinWidth, childMaxWidth);
413
414 Grid grid(const_cast<RenderGrid&>(*this));
415 GridTrackSizingAlgorithm algorithm(this, grid);
416 placeItemsOnGrid(algorithm, std::nullopt);
417
418 performGridItemsPreLayout(algorithm);
419
420 if (m_baselineItemsCached)
421 algorithm.copyBaselineItemsCache(m_trackSizingAlgorithm, GridRowAxis);
422 else {
423 for (auto* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
424 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
425 continue;
426 if (isBaselineAlignmentForChild(*child, GridRowAxis))
427 algorithm.cacheBaselineAlignedItem(*child, GridRowAxis);
428 }
429 }
430
431 computeTrackSizesForIndefiniteSize(algorithm, ForColumns, &minLogicalWidth, &maxLogicalWidth);
432
433 if (hadExcludedChildren) {
434 minLogicalWidth = std::max(minLogicalWidth, childMinWidth);
435 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(maxLogicalWidth, childMaxWidth);
436 }
437
438 LayoutUnit scrollbarWidth = intrinsicScrollbarLogicalWidth();
439 minLogicalWidth += scrollbarWidth;
440 maxLogicalWidth += scrollbarWidth;
441}
442
443void RenderGrid::computeTrackSizesForIndefiniteSize(GridTrackSizingAlgorithm& algorithm, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, LayoutUnit* minIntrinsicSize, LayoutUnit* maxIntrinsicSize) const
444{
445 const Grid& grid = algorithm.grid();
446 algorithm.setup(direction, numTracks(direction, grid), IntrinsicSizeComputation, std::nullopt);
447 algorithm.run();
448
449 size_t numberOfTracks = algorithm.tracks(direction).size();
450 LayoutUnit totalGuttersSize = guttersSize(grid, direction, 0, numberOfTracks, std::nullopt);
451
452 if (minIntrinsicSize)
453 *minIntrinsicSize = algorithm.minContentSize() + totalGuttersSize;
454 if (maxIntrinsicSize)
455 *maxIntrinsicSize = algorithm.maxContentSize() + totalGuttersSize;
456
457 ASSERT(algorithm.tracksAreWiderThanMinTrackBreadth());
458}
459
460unsigned RenderGrid::computeAutoRepeatTracksCount(GridTrackSizingDirection direction, std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableSize) const
461{
462 ASSERT(!availableSize || availableSize.value() != -1);
463 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
464 const auto& autoRepeatTracks = isRowAxis ? style().gridAutoRepeatColumns() : style().gridAutoRepeatRows();
465 unsigned autoRepeatTrackListLength = autoRepeatTracks.size();
466
467 if (!autoRepeatTrackListLength)
468 return 0;
469
470 bool needsToFulfillMinimumSize = false;
471 if (!availableSize) {
472 const Length& maxSize = isRowAxis ? style().logicalMaxWidth() : style().logicalMaxHeight();
473 std::optional<LayoutUnit> containingBlockAvailableSize;
474 std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableMaxSize;
475 if (maxSize.isSpecified()) {
476 if (maxSize.isPercentOrCalculated())
477 containingBlockAvailableSize = isRowAxis ? containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent() : containingBlockLogicalHeightForContent(ExcludeMarginBorderPadding);
478 LayoutUnit maxSizeValue = valueForLength(maxSize, containingBlockAvailableSize.value_or(LayoutUnit()));
479 availableMaxSize = isRowAxis ? adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(maxSizeValue, maxSize.type()) : adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(maxSizeValue);
480 }
481
482 const Length& minSize = isRowAxis ? style().logicalMinWidth() : style().logicalMinHeight();
483 if (!availableMaxSize && !minSize.isSpecified())
484 return autoRepeatTrackListLength;
485
486 std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableMinSize;
487 if (minSize.isSpecified()) {
488 if (!containingBlockAvailableSize && minSize.isPercentOrCalculated())
489 containingBlockAvailableSize = isRowAxis ? containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent() : containingBlockLogicalHeightForContent(ExcludeMarginBorderPadding);
490 LayoutUnit minSizeValue = valueForLength(minSize, containingBlockAvailableSize.value_or(LayoutUnit()));
491 availableMinSize = isRowAxis ? adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(minSizeValue, minSize.type()) : adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(minSizeValue);
492 if (!maxSize.isSpecified())
493 needsToFulfillMinimumSize = true;
494 }
495
496 availableSize = std::max(availableMinSize.value_or(LayoutUnit()), availableMaxSize.value_or(LayoutUnit()));
497 }
498
499 LayoutUnit autoRepeatTracksSize;
500 for (auto& autoTrackSize : autoRepeatTracks) {
501 ASSERT(autoTrackSize.minTrackBreadth().isLength());
502 ASSERT(!autoTrackSize.minTrackBreadth().isFlex());
503 bool hasDefiniteMaxTrackSizingFunction = autoTrackSize.maxTrackBreadth().isLength() && !autoTrackSize.maxTrackBreadth().isContentSized();
504 auto trackLength = hasDefiniteMaxTrackSizingFunction ? autoTrackSize.maxTrackBreadth().length() : autoTrackSize.minTrackBreadth().length();
505 autoRepeatTracksSize += valueForLength(trackLength, availableSize.value());
506 }
507 // For the purpose of finding the number of auto-repeated tracks, the UA must floor the track size to a UA-specified
508 // value to avoid division by zero. It is suggested that this floor be 1px.
509 autoRepeatTracksSize = std::max<LayoutUnit>(1_lu, autoRepeatTracksSize);
510
511 // There will be always at least 1 auto-repeat track, so take it already into account when computing the total track size.
512 LayoutUnit tracksSize = autoRepeatTracksSize;
513 auto& trackSizes = isRowAxis ? style().gridColumns() : style().gridRows();
514
515 for (const auto& track : trackSizes) {
516 bool hasDefiniteMaxTrackBreadth = track.maxTrackBreadth().isLength() && !track.maxTrackBreadth().isContentSized();
517 ASSERT(hasDefiniteMaxTrackBreadth || (track.minTrackBreadth().isLength() && !track.minTrackBreadth().isContentSized()));
518 tracksSize += valueForLength(hasDefiniteMaxTrackBreadth ? track.maxTrackBreadth().length() : track.minTrackBreadth().length(), availableSize.value());
519 }
520
521 // Add gutters as if auto repeat tracks were only repeated once. Gaps between different repetitions will be added later when
522 // computing the number of repetitions of the auto repeat().
523 LayoutUnit gapSize = gridGap(direction, availableSize);
524 tracksSize += gapSize * (trackSizes.size() + autoRepeatTrackListLength - 1);
525
526 LayoutUnit freeSpace = availableSize.value() - tracksSize;
527 if (freeSpace <= 0)
528 return autoRepeatTrackListLength;
529
530 LayoutUnit autoRepeatSizeWithGap = autoRepeatTracksSize + gapSize * autoRepeatTrackListLength;
531 unsigned repetitions = 1 + (freeSpace / autoRepeatSizeWithGap).toUnsigned();
532 freeSpace -= autoRepeatSizeWithGap * (repetitions - 1);
533 ASSERT(freeSpace >= 0);
534
535 // Provided the grid container does not have a definite size or max-size in the relevant axis,
536 // if the min size is definite then the number of repetitions is the largest possible positive
537 // integer that fulfills that minimum requirement.
538 if (needsToFulfillMinimumSize && freeSpace)
539 ++repetitions;
540
541 return repetitions * autoRepeatTrackListLength;
542}

545std::unique_ptr<OrderedTrackIndexSet> RenderGrid::computeEmptyTracksForAutoRepeat(Grid& grid, GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
546{
547 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
548 if ((isRowAxis && style().gridAutoRepeatColumnsType() != AutoRepeatType::Fit)
549 || (!isRowAxis && style().gridAutoRepeatRowsType() != AutoRepeatType::Fit))
550 return nullptr;
551
552 std::unique_ptr<OrderedTrackIndexSet> emptyTrackIndexes;
553 unsigned insertionPoint = isRowAxis ? style().gridAutoRepeatColumnsInsertionPoint() : style().gridAutoRepeatRowsInsertionPoint();
554 unsigned firstAutoRepeatTrack = insertionPoint + grid.explicitGridStart(direction);
555 unsigned lastAutoRepeatTrack = firstAutoRepeatTrack + grid.autoRepeatTracks(direction);
556
557 if (!grid.hasGridItems() || shouldApplySizeContainment(*this)) {
558 emptyTrackIndexes = makeUnique<OrderedTrackIndexSet>();
559 for (unsigned trackIndex = firstAutoRepeatTrack; trackIndex < lastAutoRepeatTrack; ++trackIndex)
560 emptyTrackIndexes->add(trackIndex);
561 } else {
562 for (unsigned trackIndex = firstAutoRepeatTrack; trackIndex < lastAutoRepeatTrack; ++trackIndex) {
563 GridIterator iterator(grid, direction, trackIndex);
564 if (!iterator.nextGridItem()) {
565 if (!emptyTrackIndexes)
566 emptyTrackIndexes = makeUnique<OrderedTrackIndexSet>();
567 emptyTrackIndexes->add(trackIndex);
568 }
569 }
570 }
571 return emptyTrackIndexes;
572}
573
574unsigned RenderGrid::clampAutoRepeatTracks(GridTrackSizingDirection direction, unsigned autoRepeatTracks) const
575{
576 if (!autoRepeatTracks)
577 return 0;
578
579 unsigned insertionPoint = direction == ForColumns ? style().gridAutoRepeatColumnsInsertionPoint() : style().gridAutoRepeatRowsInsertionPoint();
580 unsigned maxTracks = static_cast<unsigned>(GridPosition::max());
581
582 if (!insertionPoint)
583 return std::min(autoRepeatTracks, maxTracks);
584
585 if (insertionPoint >= maxTracks)
586 return 0;
587
588 return std::min(autoRepeatTracks, maxTracks - insertionPoint);
589}
590
591// FIXME: We shouldn't have to pass the available logical width as argument. The problem is that
592// availableLogicalWidth() does always return a value even if we cannot resolve it like when
593// computing the intrinsic size (preferred widths). That's why we pass the responsibility to the
594// caller who does know whether the available logical width is indefinite or not.
595void RenderGrid::placeItemsOnGrid(GridTrackSizingAlgorithm& algorithm, std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableLogicalWidth) const
596{
597 Grid& grid = algorithm.mutableGrid();
598 unsigned autoRepeatColumns = computeAutoRepeatTracksCount(ForColumns, availableLogicalWidth);
599 unsigned autoRepeatRows = computeAutoRepeatTracksCount(ForRows, availableLogicalHeightForPercentageComputation());
600
601 autoRepeatRows = clampAutoRepeatTracks(ForRows, autoRepeatRows);
602 autoRepeatColumns = clampAutoRepeatTracks(ForColumns, autoRepeatColumns);
603
604 if (autoRepeatColumns != grid.autoRepeatTracks(ForColumns) || autoRepeatRows != grid.autoRepeatTracks(ForRows)) {
605 grid.setNeedsItemsPlacement(true);
606 grid.setAutoRepeatTracks(autoRepeatRows, autoRepeatColumns);
607 }
608
609 if (!grid.needsItemsPlacement())
610 return;
611
612 ASSERT(!grid.hasGridItems());
613 populateExplicitGridAndOrderIterator(grid);
614
615 Vector<RenderBox*> autoMajorAxisAutoGridItems;
616 Vector<RenderBox*> specifiedMajorAxisAutoGridItems;
617 for (auto* child = grid.orderIterator().first(); child; child = grid.orderIterator().next()) {
618 if (grid.orderIterator().shouldSkipChild(*child))
619 continue;
620
621 // Grid items should use the grid area sizes instead of the containing block (grid container)
622 // sizes, we initialize the overrides here if needed to ensure it.
623 if (!child->hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth())
624 child->setOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth(LayoutUnit());
625 if (!child->hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight())
626 child->setOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight(std::nullopt);
627
628 GridArea area = grid.gridItemArea(*child);
629 if (!area.rows.isIndefinite())
630 area.rows.translate(grid.explicitGridStart(ForRows));
631 if (!area.columns.isIndefinite())
632 area.columns.translate(grid.explicitGridStart(ForColumns));
633
634 if (area.rows.isIndefinite() || area.columns.isIndefinite()) {
635 grid.setGridItemArea(*child, area);
636 bool majorAxisDirectionIsForColumns = autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection() == ForColumns;
637 if ((majorAxisDirectionIsForColumns && area.columns.isIndefinite())
638 || (!majorAxisDirectionIsForColumns && area.rows.isIndefinite()))
639 autoMajorAxisAutoGridItems.append(child);
640 else
641 specifiedMajorAxisAutoGridItems.append(child);
642 continue;
643 }
644 grid.insert(*child, { area.rows, area.columns });
645 }
646
647#if ASSERT_ENABLED
648 if (grid.hasGridItems()) {
649 ASSERT(grid.numTracks(ForRows) >= GridPositionsResolver::explicitGridRowCount(style(), grid.autoRepeatTracks(ForRows)));
650 ASSERT(grid.numTracks(ForColumns) >= GridPositionsResolver::explicitGridColumnCount(style(), grid.autoRepeatTracks(ForColumns)));
651 }
652#endif
653
654 placeSpecifiedMajorAxisItemsOnGrid(grid, specifiedMajorAxisAutoGridItems);
655 placeAutoMajorAxisItemsOnGrid(grid, autoMajorAxisAutoGridItems);
656
657 // Compute collapsible tracks for auto-fit.
658 grid.setAutoRepeatEmptyColumns(computeEmptyTracksForAutoRepeat(grid, ForColumns));
659 grid.setAutoRepeatEmptyRows(computeEmptyTracksForAutoRepeat(grid, ForRows));
660
661 grid.setNeedsItemsPlacement(false);
662
663#if ASSERT_ENABLED
664 for (auto* child = grid.orderIterator().first(); child; child = grid.orderIterator().next()) {
665 if (grid.orderIterator().shouldSkipChild(*child))
666 continue;
667
668 GridArea area = grid.gridItemArea(*child);
669 ASSERT(area.rows.isTranslatedDefinite() && area.columns.isTranslatedDefinite());
670 }
671#endif
672}
673
674void RenderGrid::performGridItemsPreLayout(const GridTrackSizingAlgorithm& algorithm) const
675{
676 ASSERT(!algorithm.grid().needsItemsPlacement());
677 // FIXME: We need a way when we are calling this during intrinsic size compuation before performing
678 // the layout. Maybe using the PreLayout phase ?
679 for (auto* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
680 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
681 continue;
682 // Orthogonal items should be laid out in order to properly compute content-sized tracks that may depend on item's intrinsic size.
683 // We also need to properly estimate its grid area size, since it may affect to the baseline shims if such item particiaptes in baseline alignment.
684 if (GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, *child)) {
685 updateGridAreaLogicalSize(*child, algorithm.estimatedGridAreaBreadthForChild(*child, ForColumns), algorithm.estimatedGridAreaBreadthForChild(*child, ForRows));
686 child->layoutIfNeeded();
687 continue;
688 }
689 // We need to layout the item to know whether it must synthesize its
690 // baseline or not, which may imply a cyclic sizing dependency.
691 // FIXME: Can we avoid it ?
692 if (isBaselineAlignmentForChild(*child)) {
693 updateGridAreaLogicalSize(*child, algorithm.estimatedGridAreaBreadthForChild(*child, ForColumns), algorithm.estimatedGridAreaBreadthForChild(*child, ForRows));
694 child->layoutIfNeeded();
695 }
696 }
697}
698
699void RenderGrid::populateExplicitGridAndOrderIterator(Grid& grid) const
700{
701 OrderIteratorPopulator populator(grid.orderIterator());
702 unsigned explicitRowStart = 0;
703 unsigned explicitColumnStart = 0;
704 unsigned autoRepeatRows = grid.autoRepeatTracks(ForRows);
705 unsigned autoRepeatColumns = grid.autoRepeatTracks(ForColumns);
706 unsigned maximumRowIndex = GridPositionsResolver::explicitGridRowCount(style(), autoRepeatRows);
707 unsigned maximumColumnIndex = GridPositionsResolver::explicitGridColumnCount(style(), autoRepeatColumns);
708
709 for (RenderBox* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
710 if (!populator.collectChild(*child))
711 continue;
712
713 GridSpan rowPositions = GridPositionsResolver::resolveGridPositionsFromStyle(style(), *child, ForRows, autoRepeatRows);
714 if (!rowPositions.isIndefinite()) {
715 explicitRowStart = std::max<int>(explicitRowStart, -rowPositions.untranslatedStartLine());
716 maximumRowIndex = std::max<int>(maximumRowIndex, rowPositions.untranslatedEndLine());
717 } else {
718 // Grow the grid for items with a definite row span, getting the largest such span.
719 unsigned spanSize = GridPositionsResolver::spanSizeForAutoPlacedItem(*child, ForRows);
720 maximumRowIndex = std::max(maximumRowIndex, spanSize);
721 }
722
723 GridSpan columnPositions = GridPositionsResolver::resolveGridPositionsFromStyle(style(), *child, ForColumns, autoRepeatColumns);
724 if (!columnPositions.isIndefinite()) {
725 explicitColumnStart = std::max<int>(explicitColumnStart, -columnPositions.untranslatedStartLine());
726 maximumColumnIndex = std::max<int>(maximumColumnIndex, columnPositions.untranslatedEndLine());
727 } else {
728 // Grow the grid for items with a definite column span, getting the largest such span.
729 unsigned spanSize = GridPositionsResolver::spanSizeForAutoPlacedItem(*child, ForColumns);
730 maximumColumnIndex = std::max(maximumColumnIndex, spanSize);
731 }
732
733 grid.setGridItemArea(*child, { rowPositions, columnPositions });
734 }
735
736 grid.setExplicitGridStart(explicitRowStart, explicitColumnStart);
737 grid.ensureGridSize(maximumRowIndex + explicitRowStart, maximumColumnIndex + explicitColumnStart);
738}
739
740std::unique_ptr<GridArea> RenderGrid::createEmptyGridAreaAtSpecifiedPositionsOutsideGrid(Grid& grid, const RenderBox& gridItem, GridTrackSizingDirection specifiedDirection, const GridSpan& specifiedPositions) const
741{
742 GridTrackSizingDirection crossDirection = specifiedDirection == ForColumns ? ForRows : ForColumns;
743 const unsigned endOfCrossDirection = grid.numTracks(crossDirection);
744 unsigned crossDirectionSpanSize = GridPositionsResolver::spanSizeForAutoPlacedItem(gridItem, crossDirection);
745 GridSpan crossDirectionPositions = GridSpan::translatedDefiniteGridSpan(endOfCrossDirection, endOfCrossDirection + crossDirectionSpanSize);
746 return makeUnique<GridArea>(specifiedDirection == ForColumns ? crossDirectionPositions : specifiedPositions, specifiedDirection == ForColumns ? specifiedPositions : crossDirectionPositions);
747}
748
749void RenderGrid::placeSpecifiedMajorAxisItemsOnGrid(Grid& grid, const Vector<RenderBox*>& autoGridItems) const
750{
751 bool isForColumns = autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection() == ForColumns;
752 bool isGridAutoFlowDense = style().isGridAutoFlowAlgorithmDense();
753
754 // Mapping between the major axis tracks (rows or columns) and the last auto-placed item's position inserted on
755 // that track. This is needed to implement "sparse" packing for items locked to a given track.
756 // See http://dev.w3.org/csswg/css-grid/#auto-placement-algorithm
757 HashMap<unsigned, unsigned, DefaultHash<unsigned>, WTF::UnsignedWithZeroKeyHashTraits<unsigned>> minorAxisCursors;
758
759 for (auto& autoGridItem : autoGridItems) {
760 GridSpan majorAxisPositions = grid.gridItemSpan(*autoGridItem, autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection());
761 ASSERT(majorAxisPositions.isTranslatedDefinite());
762 ASSERT(grid.gridItemSpan(*autoGridItem, autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection()).isIndefinite());
763 unsigned minorAxisSpanSize = GridPositionsResolver::spanSizeForAutoPlacedItem(*autoGridItem, autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection());
764 unsigned majorAxisInitialPosition = majorAxisPositions.startLine();
765
766 GridIterator iterator(grid, autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection(), majorAxisPositions.startLine(), isGridAutoFlowDense ? 0 : minorAxisCursors.get(majorAxisInitialPosition));
767 std::unique_ptr<GridArea> emptyGridArea = iterator.nextEmptyGridArea(majorAxisPositions.integerSpan(), minorAxisSpanSize);
768 if (!emptyGridArea)
769 emptyGridArea = createEmptyGridAreaAtSpecifiedPositionsOutsideGrid(grid, *autoGridItem, autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection(), majorAxisPositions);
770
771 grid.insert(*autoGridItem, *emptyGridArea);
772
773 if (!isGridAutoFlowDense)
774 minorAxisCursors.set(majorAxisInitialPosition, isForColumns ? emptyGridArea->rows.startLine() : emptyGridArea->columns.startLine());
775 }
776}
777
778void RenderGrid::placeAutoMajorAxisItemsOnGrid(Grid& grid, const Vector<RenderBox*>& autoGridItems) const
779{
780 AutoPlacementCursor autoPlacementCursor = {0, 0};
781 bool isGridAutoFlowDense = style().isGridAutoFlowAlgorithmDense();
782
783 for (auto& autoGridItem : autoGridItems) {
784 placeAutoMajorAxisItemOnGrid(grid, *autoGridItem, autoPlacementCursor);
785
786 if (isGridAutoFlowDense) {
787 autoPlacementCursor.first = 0;
788 autoPlacementCursor.second = 0;
789 }
790 }
791}
792
793void RenderGrid::placeAutoMajorAxisItemOnGrid(Grid& grid, RenderBox& gridItem, AutoPlacementCursor& autoPlacementCursor) const
794{
795 ASSERT(grid.gridItemSpan(gridItem, autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection()).isIndefinite());
796 unsigned majorAxisSpanSize = GridPositionsResolver::spanSizeForAutoPlacedItem(gridItem, autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection());
797
798 const unsigned endOfMajorAxis = grid.numTracks(autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection());
799 unsigned majorAxisAutoPlacementCursor = autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection() == ForColumns ? autoPlacementCursor.second : autoPlacementCursor.first;
800 unsigned minorAxisAutoPlacementCursor = autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection() == ForColumns ? autoPlacementCursor.first : autoPlacementCursor.second;
801
802 std::unique_ptr<GridArea> emptyGridArea;
803 GridSpan minorAxisPositions = grid.gridItemSpan(gridItem, autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection());
804 if (minorAxisPositions.isTranslatedDefinite()) {
805 // Move to the next track in major axis if initial position in minor axis is before auto-placement cursor.
806 if (minorAxisPositions.startLine() < minorAxisAutoPlacementCursor)
807 majorAxisAutoPlacementCursor++;
808
809 if (majorAxisAutoPlacementCursor < endOfMajorAxis) {
810 GridIterator iterator(grid, autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection(), minorAxisPositions.startLine(), majorAxisAutoPlacementCursor);
811 emptyGridArea = iterator.nextEmptyGridArea(minorAxisPositions.integerSpan(), majorAxisSpanSize);
812 }
813
814 if (!emptyGridArea)
815 emptyGridArea = createEmptyGridAreaAtSpecifiedPositionsOutsideGrid(grid, gridItem, autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection(), minorAxisPositions);
816 } else {
817 unsigned minorAxisSpanSize = GridPositionsResolver::spanSizeForAutoPlacedItem(gridItem, autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection());
818
819 for (unsigned majorAxisIndex = majorAxisAutoPlacementCursor; majorAxisIndex < endOfMajorAxis; ++majorAxisIndex) {
820 GridIterator iterator(grid, autoPlacementMajorAxisDirection(), majorAxisIndex, minorAxisAutoPlacementCursor);
821 emptyGridArea = iterator.nextEmptyGridArea(majorAxisSpanSize, minorAxisSpanSize);
822
823 if (emptyGridArea) {
824 // Check that it fits in the minor axis direction, as we shouldn't grow in that direction here (it was already managed in populateExplicitGridAndOrderIterator()).
825 unsigned minorAxisFinalPositionIndex = autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection() == ForColumns ? emptyGridArea->columns.endLine() : emptyGridArea->rows.endLine();
826 const unsigned endOfMinorAxis = grid.numTracks(autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection());
827 if (minorAxisFinalPositionIndex <= endOfMinorAxis)
828 break;
829
830 // Discard empty grid area as it does not fit in the minor axis direction.
831 // We don't need to create a new empty grid area yet as we might find a valid one in the next iteration.
832 emptyGridArea = nullptr;
833 }
834
835 // As we're moving to the next track in the major axis we should reset the auto-placement cursor in the minor axis.
836 minorAxisAutoPlacementCursor = 0;
837 }
838
839 if (!emptyGridArea)
840 emptyGridArea = createEmptyGridAreaAtSpecifiedPositionsOutsideGrid(grid, gridItem, autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection(), GridSpan::translatedDefiniteGridSpan(0, minorAxisSpanSize));
841 }
842
843 grid.insert(gridItem, *emptyGridArea);
844 autoPlacementCursor.first = emptyGridArea->rows.startLine();
845 autoPlacementCursor.second = emptyGridArea->columns.startLine();
846}
847

853GridTrackSizingDirection RenderGrid::autoPlacementMinorAxisDirection() const

855 return style().isGridAutoFlowDirectionColumn() ? ForRows : ForColumns;

865
866Vector<LayoutUnit> RenderGrid::trackSizesForComputedStyle(GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
867{
868 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
869 auto& positions = isRowAxis ? m_columnPositions : m_rowPositions;
870 size_t numPositions = positions.size();
871 LayoutUnit offsetBetweenTracks = isRowAxis ? m_offsetBetweenColumns.distributionOffset : m_offsetBetweenRows.distributionOffset;
872
873 Vector<LayoutUnit> tracks;
874 if (numPositions < 2)
875 return tracks;
876
877 ASSERT(!m_grid.needsItemsPlacement());
878 bool hasCollapsedTracks = m_grid.hasAutoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction);
879 LayoutUnit gap = !hasCollapsedTracks ? gridGap(direction) : 0_lu;
880 tracks.reserveCapacity(numPositions - 1);
881 for (size_t i = 0; i < numPositions - 2; ++i)
882 tracks.append(positions[i + 1] - positions[i] - offsetBetweenTracks - gap);
883 tracks.append(positions[numPositions - 1] - positions[numPositions - 2]);
884
885 if (!hasCollapsedTracks)
886 return tracks;
887
888 size_t remainingEmptyTracks = m_grid.autoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction)->size();
889 size_t lastLine = tracks.size();
890 gap = gridGap(direction);
891 for (size_t i = 1; i < lastLine; ++i) {
892 if (m_grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, i - 1))
893 --remainingEmptyTracks;
894 else {
895 // Remove the gap between consecutive non empty tracks. Remove it also just once for an
896 // arbitrary number of empty tracks between two non empty ones.
897 bool allRemainingTracksAreEmpty = remainingEmptyTracks == (lastLine - i);
898 if (!allRemainingTracksAreEmpty || !m_grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, i))
899 tracks[i - 1] -= gap;
900 }
901 }
902
903 return tracks;
904}

912static bool overrideSizeChanged(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, std::optional<LayoutUnit> width, std::optional<LayoutUnit> height)
913{
914 if (direction == ForColumns)
915 return !child.hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth() || child.overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth() != width;
916 return !child.hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight() || child.overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight() != height;

924void RenderGrid::updateGridAreaLogicalSize(RenderBox& child, std::optional<LayoutUnit> width, std::optional<LayoutUnit> height) const
925{
926 // Because the grid area cannot be styled, we don't need to adjust
927 // the grid breadth to account for 'box-sizing'.
928 bool gridAreaWidthChanged = overrideSizeChanged(child, ForColumns, width, height);
929 bool gridAreaHeightChanged = overrideSizeChanged(child, ForRows, width, height);
930 if (gridAreaWidthChanged || (gridAreaHeightChanged && hasRelativeBlockAxisSize(*this, child)))
931 child.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
932
933 child.setOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth(width);
934 child.setOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight(height);
935}
936
937void RenderGrid::layoutGridItems()
938{
939 populateGridPositionsForDirection(ForColumns);
940 populateGridPositionsForDirection(ForRows);
941
942 for (RenderBox* child = firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
943
944 if (m_grid.orderIterator().shouldSkipChild(*child)) {
945 if (child->isOutOfFlowPositioned())
946 prepareChildForPositionedLayout(*child);
947 continue;
948 }
949
950 // Setting the definite grid area's sizes. It may imply that the
951 // item must perform a layout if its area differs from the one
952 // used during the track sizing algorithm.
953 updateGridAreaLogicalSize(*child, gridAreaBreadthForChildIncludingAlignmentOffsets(*child, ForColumns), gridAreaBreadthForChildIncludingAlignmentOffsets(*child, ForRows));
954
955 LayoutRect oldChildRect = child->frameRect();
956
957 // Stretching logic might force a child layout, so we need to run it before the layoutIfNeeded
958 // call to avoid unnecessary relayouts. This might imply that child margins, needed to correctly
959 // determine the available space before stretching, are not set yet.
960 applyStretchAlignmentToChildIfNeeded(*child);
961
962 child->layoutIfNeeded();
963
964 // We need pending layouts to be done in order to compute auto-margins properly.
965 updateAutoMarginsInColumnAxisIfNeeded(*child);
966 updateAutoMarginsInRowAxisIfNeeded(*child);
967
968 setLogicalPositionForChild(*child);
969
970 // If the child moved, we have to repaint it as well as any floating/positioned
971 // descendants. An exception is if we need a layout. In this case, we know we're going to
972 // repaint ourselves (and the child) anyway.
973 if (!selfNeedsLayout() && child->checkForRepaintDuringLayout())
974 child->repaintDuringLayoutIfMoved(oldChildRect);
975 }
976}
977
978void RenderGrid::prepareChildForPositionedLayout(RenderBox& child)
979{
980 ASSERT(child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
981 child.containingBlock()->insertPositionedObject(child);
982
983 RenderLayer* childLayer = child.layer();
984 // Static position of a positioned child should use the content-box (https://drafts.csswg.org/css-grid/#static-position).
985 childLayer->setStaticInlinePosition(borderAndPaddingStart());
986 childLayer->setStaticBlockPosition(borderAndPaddingBefore());
987}

989bool RenderGrid::hasStaticPositionForChild(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
990{
991 return direction == ForColumns ? child.style().hasStaticInlinePosition(isHorizontalWritingMode()) : child.style().hasStaticBlockPosition(isHorizontalWritingMode());
992}
993
994void RenderGrid::layoutPositionedObject(RenderBox& child, bool relayoutChildren, bool fixedPositionObjectsOnly)
995{
996 LayoutUnit columnBreadth = gridAreaBreadthForOutOfFlowChild(child, ForColumns);
997 LayoutUnit rowBreadth = gridAreaBreadthForOutOfFlowChild(child, ForRows);
998
999 child.setOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth(columnBreadth);
1000 child.setOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight(rowBreadth);
1001
1002 // Mark for layout as we're resetting the position before and we relay in generic layout logic
1003 // for positioned items in order to get the offsets properly resolved.
1004 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1005
1006 RenderBlock::layoutPositionedObject(child, relayoutChildren, fixedPositionObjectsOnly);
1007
1008 setLogicalOffsetForChild(child, ForColumns);
1009 setLogicalOffsetForChild(child, ForRows);
1010}
1011
1012LayoutUnit RenderGrid::gridAreaBreadthForChildIncludingAlignmentOffsets(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
1013{
1014 // We need the cached value when available because Content Distribution alignment properties
1015 // may have some influence in the final grid area breadth.
1016 const auto& tracks = m_trackSizingAlgorithm.tracks(direction);
1017 const auto& span = m_grid.gridItemSpan(child, direction);
1018 const auto& linePositions = (direction == ForColumns) ? m_columnPositions : m_rowPositions;
1019
1020 LayoutUnit initialTrackPosition = linePositions[span.startLine()];
1021 LayoutUnit finalTrackPosition = linePositions[span.endLine() - 1];
1022
1023 // Track Positions vector stores the 'start' grid line of each track, so we have to add last track's baseSize.
1024 return finalTrackPosition - initialTrackPosition + tracks[span.endLine() - 1].baseSize();
1025}
1026
1027void RenderGrid::populateGridPositionsForDirection(GridTrackSizingDirection direction)
1028{
1029 // Since we add alignment offsets and track gutters, grid lines are not always adjacent. Hence we will have to
1030 // assume from now on that we just store positions of the initial grid lines of each track,
1031 // except the last one, which is the only one considered as a final grid line of a track.
1032
1033 // The grid container's frame elements (border, padding and <content-position> offset) are sensible to the
1034 // inline-axis flow direction. However, column lines positions are 'direction' unaware. This simplification
1035 // allows us to use the same indexes to identify the columns independently on the inline-axis direction.
1036 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
1037 auto& tracks = m_trackSizingAlgorithm.tracks(direction);
1038 unsigned numberOfTracks = tracks.size();
1039 unsigned numberOfLines = numberOfTracks + 1;
1040 unsigned lastLine = numberOfLines - 1;
1041 bool hasCollapsedTracks = m_grid.hasAutoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction);
1042 size_t numberOfCollapsedTracks = hasCollapsedTracks ? m_grid.autoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction)->size() : 0;
1043 const auto& offset = direction == ForColumns ? m_offsetBetweenColumns : m_offsetBetweenRows;
1044 auto& positions = isRowAxis ? m_columnPositions : m_rowPositions;
1045 positions.resize(numberOfLines);
1046
1047 auto borderAndPadding = isRowAxis ? borderAndPaddingLogicalLeft() : borderAndPaddingBefore();
1048#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1049 // FIXME: Ideally scrollbarLogicalWidth() should return zero in iOS so we don't need this
1050 // (see bug https://webkit.org/b/191857).
1051 // If we are in horizontal writing mode and RTL direction the scrollbar is painted on the left,
1052 // so we need to take into account when computing the position of the columns.
1053 if (isRowAxis && style().isHorizontalWritingMode() && !style().isLeftToRightDirection())
1054 borderAndPadding += scrollbarLogicalWidth();
1055#endif
1056
1057 positions[0] = borderAndPadding + offset.positionOffset;
1058 if (numberOfLines > 1) {
1059 // If we have collapsed tracks we just ignore gaps here and add them later as we might not
1060 // compute the gap between two consecutive tracks without examining the surrounding ones.
1061 LayoutUnit gap = !hasCollapsedTracks ? gridGap(direction) : 0_lu;
1062 unsigned nextToLastLine = numberOfLines - 2;
1063 for (unsigned i = 0; i < nextToLastLine; ++i)
1064 positions[i + 1] = positions[i] + offset.distributionOffset + tracks[i].baseSize() + gap;
1065 positions[lastLine] = positions[nextToLastLine] + tracks[nextToLastLine].baseSize();
1066
1067 // Adjust collapsed gaps. Collapsed tracks cause the surrounding gutters to collapse (they
1068 // coincide exactly) except on the edges of the grid where they become 0.
1069 if (hasCollapsedTracks) {
1070 gap = gridGap(direction);
1071 unsigned remainingEmptyTracks = numberOfCollapsedTracks;
1072 LayoutUnit offsetAccumulator;
1073 LayoutUnit gapAccumulator;
1074 for (unsigned i = 1; i < lastLine; ++i) {
1075 if (m_grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, i - 1)) {
1076 --remainingEmptyTracks;
1077 offsetAccumulator += offset.distributionOffset;
1078 } else {
1079 // Add gap between consecutive non empty tracks. Add it also just once for an
1080 // arbitrary number of empty tracks between two non empty ones.
1081 bool allRemainingTracksAreEmpty = remainingEmptyTracks == (lastLine - i);
1082 if (!allRemainingTracksAreEmpty || !m_grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, i))
1083 gapAccumulator += gap;
1084 }
1085 positions[i] += gapAccumulator - offsetAccumulator;
1086 }
1087 positions[lastLine] += gapAccumulator - offsetAccumulator;
1088 }
1089 }
1090}
1091
1092static LayoutUnit computeOverflowAlignmentOffset(OverflowAlignment overflow, LayoutUnit trackSize, LayoutUnit childSize)
1093{
1094 LayoutUnit offset = trackSize - childSize;
1095 switch (overflow) {
1096 case OverflowAlignment::Safe:
1097 // If overflow is 'safe', we have to make sure we don't overflow the 'start'
1098 // edge (potentially cause some data loss as the overflow is unreachable).
1099 return std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, offset);
1100 case OverflowAlignment::Unsafe:
1101 case OverflowAlignment::Default:
1102 // If we overflow our alignment container and overflow is 'true' (default), we
1103 // ignore the overflow and just return the value regardless (which may cause data
1104 // loss as we overflow the 'start' edge).
1105 return offset;
1106 }
1107
1108 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1109 return 0;
1110}
1111
1112LayoutUnit RenderGrid::availableAlignmentSpaceForChildBeforeStretching(LayoutUnit gridAreaBreadthForChild, const RenderBox& child) const
1113{
1114 // Because we want to avoid multiple layouts, stretching logic might be performed before
1115 // children are laid out, so we can't use the child cached values. Hence, we need to
1116 // compute margins in order to determine the available height before stretching.
1117 GridTrackSizingDirection childBlockFlowDirection = GridLayoutFunctions::flowAwareDirectionForChild(*this, child, ForRows);
1118 return std::max(0_lu, gridAreaBreadthForChild - GridLayoutFunctions::marginLogicalSizeForChild(*this, childBlockFlowDirection, child));
1119}

1135// FIXME: This logic is shared by RenderFlexibleBox, so it should be moved to RenderBox.
1136void RenderGrid::applyStretchAlignmentToChildIfNeeded(RenderBox& child)
1137{
1138 ASSERT(child.overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight());
1139
1140 // We clear height override values because we will decide now whether it's allowed or
1141 // not, evaluating the conditions which might have changed since the old values were set.
1142 child.clearOverridingLogicalHeight();
1143
1144 GridTrackSizingDirection childBlockDirection = GridLayoutFunctions::flowAwareDirectionForChild(*this, child, ForRows);
1145 bool blockFlowIsColumnAxis = childBlockDirection == ForRows;
1146 bool allowedToStretchChildBlockSize = blockFlowIsColumnAxis ? allowedToStretchChildAlongColumnAxis(child) : allowedToStretchChildAlongRowAxis(child);
1147 if (allowedToStretchChildBlockSize) {
1148 LayoutUnit stretchedLogicalHeight = availableAlignmentSpaceForChildBeforeStretching(GridLayoutFunctions::overridingContainingBlockContentSizeForChild(child, childBlockDirection).value(), child);
1149 LayoutUnit desiredLogicalHeight = child.constrainLogicalHeightByMinMax(stretchedLogicalHeight, std::nullopt);
1150 child.setOverridingLogicalHeight(desiredLogicalHeight);
1151
1152 // Checking the logical-height of a child isn't enough. Setting an override logical-height
1153 // changes the definiteness, resulting in percentages to resolve differently.
1154 //
1155 // FIXME: Can avoid laying out here in some cases. See https://webkit.org/b/87905.
1156 if (desiredLogicalHeight != child.logicalHeight() || (is<RenderBlock>(child) && downcast<RenderBlock>(child).hasPercentHeightDescendants())) {
1157 child.setLogicalHeight(0_lu);
1158 child.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1159 }
1160 }
1161}

1178
1179// FIXME: This logic is shared by RenderFlexibleBox, so it should be moved to RenderBox.
1180void RenderGrid::updateAutoMarginsInRowAxisIfNeeded(RenderBox& child)
1181{
1182 ASSERT(!child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1183
1184 const RenderStyle& parentStyle = style();
1185 Length marginStart = child.style().marginStartUsing(&parentStyle);
1186 Length marginEnd = child.style().marginEndUsing(&parentStyle);
1187 LayoutUnit marginLogicalWidth;
1188 // We should only consider computed margins if their specified value isn't
1189 // 'auto', since such computed value may come from a previous layout and may
1190 // be incorrect now.
1191 if (!marginStart.isAuto())
1192 marginLogicalWidth += child.marginStart();
1193 if (!marginEnd.isAuto())
1194 marginLogicalWidth += child.marginEnd();
1195
1196 LayoutUnit availableAlignmentSpace = child.overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth().value() - child.logicalWidth() - marginLogicalWidth;
1197 if (availableAlignmentSpace <= 0)
1198 return;
1199
1200 if (marginStart.isAuto() && marginEnd.isAuto()) {
1201 child.setMarginStart(availableAlignmentSpace / 2, &parentStyle);
1202 child.setMarginEnd(availableAlignmentSpace / 2, &parentStyle);
1203 } else if (marginStart.isAuto()) {
1204 child.setMarginStart(availableAlignmentSpace, &parentStyle);
1205 } else if (marginEnd.isAuto()) {
1206 child.setMarginEnd(availableAlignmentSpace, &parentStyle);
1207 }
1208}

1210// FIXME: This logic is shared by RenderFlexibleBox, so it should be moved to RenderBox.
1211void RenderGrid::updateAutoMarginsInColumnAxisIfNeeded(RenderBox& child)
1212{
1213 ASSERT(!child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1214
1215 const RenderStyle& parentStyle = style();
1216 Length marginBefore = child.style().marginBeforeUsing(&parentStyle);
1217 Length marginAfter = child.style().marginAfterUsing(&parentStyle);
1218 LayoutUnit marginLogicalHeight;
1219 // We should only consider computed margins if their specified value isn't
1220 // 'auto', since such computed value may come from a previous layout and may
1221 // be incorrect now.
1222 if (!marginBefore.isAuto())
1223 marginLogicalHeight += child.marginBefore();
1224 if (!marginAfter.isAuto())
1225 marginLogicalHeight += child.marginAfter();
1226
1227 LayoutUnit availableAlignmentSpace = child.overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight().value() - child.logicalHeight() - marginLogicalHeight;
1228 if (availableAlignmentSpace <= 0)
1229 return;
1230
1231 if (marginBefore.isAuto() && marginAfter.isAuto()) {
1232 child.setMarginBefore(availableAlignmentSpace / 2, &parentStyle);
1233 child.setMarginAfter(availableAlignmentSpace / 2, &parentStyle);
1234 } else if (marginBefore.isAuto()) {
1235 child.setMarginBefore(availableAlignmentSpace, &parentStyle);
1236 } else if (marginAfter.isAuto()) {
1237 child.setMarginAfter(availableAlignmentSpace, &parentStyle);
1238 }

1266
1267std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderGrid::firstLineBaseline() const
1268{
1269 if (isWritingModeRoot() || !m_grid.hasGridItems() || shouldApplyLayoutContainment(*this))
1270 return std::nullopt;
1271
1272 const RenderBox* baselineChild = nullptr;
1273 // Finding the first grid item in grid order.
1274 unsigned numColumns = m_grid.numTracks(ForColumns);
1275 for (size_t column = 0; column < numColumns; column++) {
1276 for (auto& child : m_grid.cell(0, column)) {
1277 ASSERT(child.get());
1278 // If an item participates in baseline alignment, we select such item.
1279 if (isBaselineAlignmentForChild(*child, GridColumnAxis, FirstLine)) {
1280 // FIXME: self-baseline and content-baseline alignment not implemented yet.
1281 baselineChild = child.get();
1282 break;
1283 }
1284 if (!baselineChild)
1285 baselineChild = child.get();
1286 }
1287 }
1288
1289 if (!baselineChild)
1290 return std::nullopt;
1291
1292 auto baseline = GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, *baselineChild) ? std::nullopt : baselineChild->firstLineBaseline();
1293 // We take border-box's bottom if no valid baseline.
1294 if (!baseline) {
1295 // FIXME: We should pass |direction| into firstLineBaseline and stop bailing out if we're a writing
1296 // mode root. This would also fix some cases where the grid is orthogonal to its container.
1297 LineDirectionMode direction = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? HorizontalLine : VerticalLine;
1298 return synthesizedBaselineFromBorderBox(*baselineChild, direction) + logicalTopForChild(*baselineChild);
1299 }
1300 return baseline.value() + baselineChild->logicalTop().toInt();
1301}

1304{
1305 return firstLineBaseline();

1317
1318GridAxisPosition RenderGrid::columnAxisPositionForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
1319{
1320 bool hasSameWritingMode = child.style().writingMode() == style().writingMode();
1321 bool childIsLTR = child.style().isLeftToRightDirection();
1322 if (child.isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !hasStaticPositionForChild(child, ForRows))
1323 return GridAxisStart;
1324
1325 switch (alignSelfForChild(child).position()) {
1326 case ItemPosition::SelfStart:
1327 // FIXME: Should we implement this logic in a generic utility function ?
1328 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the edge of the alignment container
1329 // corresponding to the alignment subject's 'start' side in the column axis.
1330 if (GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, child)) {
1331 // If orthogonal writing-modes, self-start will be based on the child's inline-axis
1332 // direction (inline-start), because it's the one parallel to the column axis.
1333 if (style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
1334 return childIsLTR ? GridAxisEnd : GridAxisStart;
1335 return childIsLTR ? GridAxisStart : GridAxisEnd;
1336 }
1337 // self-start is based on the child's block-flow direction. That's why we need to check against the grid container's block-flow direction.
1338 return hasSameWritingMode ? GridAxisStart : GridAxisEnd;
1339 case ItemPosition::SelfEnd:
1340 // FIXME: Should we implement this logic in a generic utility function ?
1341 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the edge of the alignment container
1342 // corresponding to the alignment subject's 'end' side in the column axis.
1343 if (GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, child)) {
1344 // If orthogonal writing-modes, self-end will be based on the child's inline-axis
1345 // direction, (inline-end) because it's the one parallel to the column axis.
1346 if (style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
1347 return childIsLTR ? GridAxisStart : GridAxisEnd;
1348 return childIsLTR ? GridAxisEnd : GridAxisStart;
1349 }
1350 // self-end is based on the child's block-flow direction. That's why we need to check against the grid container's block-flow direction.
1351 return hasSameWritingMode ? GridAxisEnd : GridAxisStart;
1352 case ItemPosition::Left:
1353 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the alignment container's 'line-left' edge.
1354 // The alignment axis (column axis) is always orthogonal to the inline axis, hence this value behaves as 'start'.
1355 return GridAxisStart;
1356 case ItemPosition::Right:
1357 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the alignment container's 'line-right' edge.
1358 // The alignment axis (column axis) is always orthogonal to the inline axis, hence this value behaves as 'start'.
1359 return GridAxisStart;
1360 case ItemPosition::Center:
1361 return GridAxisCenter;
1362 case ItemPosition::FlexStart: // Only used in flex layout, otherwise equivalent to 'start'.
1363 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the alignment container's 'start' edge (block-start) in the column axis.
1364 case ItemPosition::Start:
1365 return GridAxisStart;
1366 case ItemPosition::FlexEnd: // Only used in flex layout, otherwise equivalent to 'end'.
1367 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the alignment container's 'end' edge (block-end) in the column axis.
1368 case ItemPosition::End:
1369 return GridAxisEnd;
1370 case ItemPosition::Stretch:
1371 return GridAxisStart;
1372 case ItemPosition::Baseline:
1373 case ItemPosition::LastBaseline:
1374 // FIXME: Implement the previous values. For now, we always 'start' align the child.
1375 return GridAxisStart;
1376 case ItemPosition::Legacy:
1377 case ItemPosition::Auto:
1378 case ItemPosition::Normal:
1379 break;
1380 }
1381
1382 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1383 return GridAxisStart;
1384}
1385
1386GridAxisPosition RenderGrid::rowAxisPositionForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
1387{
1388 bool hasSameDirection = child.style().direction() == style().direction();
1389 bool gridIsLTR = style().isLeftToRightDirection();
1390 if (child.isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !hasStaticPositionForChild(child, ForColumns))
1391 return GridAxisStart;
1392
1393 switch (justifySelfForChild(child).position()) {
1394 case ItemPosition::SelfStart:
1395 // FIXME: Should we implement this logic in a generic utility function ?
1396 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the edge of the alignment container
1397 // corresponding to the alignment subject's 'start' side in the row axis.
1398 if (GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, child)) {
1399 // If orthogonal writing-modes, self-start will be based on the child's block-axis
1400 // direction, because it's the one parallel to the row axis.
1401 if (child.style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
1402 return gridIsLTR ? GridAxisEnd : GridAxisStart;
1403 return gridIsLTR ? GridAxisStart : GridAxisEnd;
1404 }
1405 // self-start is based on the child's inline-flow direction. That's why we need to check against the grid container's direction.
1406 return hasSameDirection ? GridAxisStart : GridAxisEnd;
1407 case ItemPosition::SelfEnd:
1408 // FIXME: Should we implement this logic in a generic utility function ?
1409 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the edge of the alignment container
1410 // corresponding to the alignment subject's 'end' side in the row axis.
1411 if (GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, child)) {
1412 // If orthogonal writing-modes, self-end will be based on the child's block-axis
1413 // direction, because it's the one parallel to the row axis.
1414 if (child.style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
1415 return gridIsLTR ? GridAxisStart : GridAxisEnd;
1416 return gridIsLTR ? GridAxisEnd : GridAxisStart;
1417 }
1418 // self-end is based on the child's inline-flow direction. That's why we need to check against the grid container's direction.
1419 return hasSameDirection ? GridAxisEnd : GridAxisStart;
1420 case ItemPosition::Left:
1421 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the alignment container's 'line-left' edge.
1422 // We want the physical 'left' side, so we have to take account, container's inline-flow direction.
1423 return gridIsLTR ? GridAxisStart : GridAxisEnd;
1424 case ItemPosition::Right:
1425 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the alignment container's 'line-right' edge.
1426 // We want the physical 'right' side, so we have to take account, container's inline-flow direction.
1427 return gridIsLTR ? GridAxisEnd : GridAxisStart;
1428 case ItemPosition::Center:
1429 return GridAxisCenter;
1430 case ItemPosition::FlexStart: // Only used in flex layout, otherwise equivalent to 'start'.
1431 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the alignment container's 'start' edge (inline-start) in the row axis.
1432 case ItemPosition::Start:
1433 return GridAxisStart;
1434 case ItemPosition::FlexEnd: // Only used in flex layout, otherwise equivalent to 'end'.
1435 // Aligns the alignment subject to be flush with the alignment container's 'end' edge (inline-end) in the row axis.
1436 case ItemPosition::End:
1437 return GridAxisEnd;
1438 case ItemPosition::Stretch:
1439 return GridAxisStart;
1440 case ItemPosition::Baseline:
1441 case ItemPosition::LastBaseline:
1442 // FIXME: Implement the previous values. For now, we always 'start' align the child.
1443 return GridAxisStart;
1444 case ItemPosition::Legacy:
1445 case ItemPosition::Auto:
1446 case ItemPosition::Normal:
1447 break;
1448 }
1449
1450 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1451 return GridAxisStart;
1452}
1453
1454LayoutUnit RenderGrid::columnAxisOffsetForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
1455{
1456 LayoutUnit startOfRow;
1457 LayoutUnit endOfRow;
1458 gridAreaPositionForChild(child, ForRows, startOfRow, endOfRow);
1459 LayoutUnit startPosition = startOfRow + marginBeforeForChild(child);
1460 if (hasAutoMarginsInColumnAxis(child))
1461 return startPosition;
1462 GridAxisPosition axisPosition = columnAxisPositionForChild(child);
1463 switch (axisPosition) {
1464 case GridAxisStart:
1465 return startPosition + columnAxisBaselineOffsetForChild(child);
1466 case GridAxisEnd:
1467 case GridAxisCenter: {
1468 LayoutUnit columnAxisChildSize = GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, child) ? child.logicalWidth() + child.marginLogicalWidth() : child.logicalHeight() + child.marginLogicalHeight();
1469 auto overflow = alignSelfForChild(child).overflow();
1470 LayoutUnit offsetFromStartPosition = computeOverflowAlignmentOffset(overflow, endOfRow - startOfRow, columnAxisChildSize);
1471 return startPosition + (axisPosition == GridAxisEnd ? offsetFromStartPosition : offsetFromStartPosition / 2);
1472 }
1473 }
1474
1475 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1476 return 0;
1477}
1478
1479LayoutUnit RenderGrid::rowAxisOffsetForChild(const RenderBox& child) const
1480{
1481 LayoutUnit startOfColumn;
1482 LayoutUnit endOfColumn;
1483 gridAreaPositionForChild(child, ForColumns, startOfColumn, endOfColumn);
1484 LayoutUnit startPosition = startOfColumn + marginStartForChild(child);
1485 if (hasAutoMarginsInRowAxis(child))
1486 return startPosition;
1487 GridAxisPosition axisPosition = rowAxisPositionForChild(child);
1488 switch (axisPosition) {
1489 case GridAxisStart:
1490 return startPosition + rowAxisBaselineOffsetForChild(child);
1491 case GridAxisEnd:
1492 case GridAxisCenter: {
1493 LayoutUnit rowAxisChildSize = GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, child) ? child.logicalHeight() + child.marginLogicalHeight() : child.logicalWidth() + child.marginLogicalWidth();
1494 auto overflow = justifySelfForChild(child).overflow();
1495 LayoutUnit offsetFromStartPosition = computeOverflowAlignmentOffset(overflow, endOfColumn - startOfColumn, rowAxisChildSize);
1496 return startPosition + (axisPosition == GridAxisEnd ? offsetFromStartPosition : offsetFromStartPosition / 2);
1497 }
1498 }
1499
1500 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1501 return 0;
1502}
1503
1504LayoutUnit RenderGrid::resolveAutoStartGridPosition(GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
1505{
1506 if (direction == ForRows || style().isLeftToRightDirection())
1507 return 0_lu;
1508
1509 int lastLine = numTracks(ForColumns, m_grid);
1510 ContentPosition position = style().resolvedJustifyContentPosition(contentAlignmentNormalBehaviorGrid());
1511 if (position == ContentPosition::End)
1512 return m_columnPositions[lastLine] - clientLogicalWidth();
1513 if (position == ContentPosition::Start || style().resolvedJustifyContentDistribution(contentAlignmentNormalBehaviorGrid()) == ContentDistribution::Stretch)
1514 return m_columnPositions[0] - borderAndPaddingLogicalLeft();
1515 return 0_lu;
1516}
1517
1518LayoutUnit RenderGrid::resolveAutoEndGridPosition(GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
1519{
1520 if (direction == ForRows)
1521 return clientLogicalHeight();
1522 if (style().isLeftToRightDirection())
1523 return clientLogicalWidth();
1524
1525 int lastLine = numTracks(ForColumns, m_grid);
1526 ContentPosition position = style().resolvedJustifyContentPosition(contentAlignmentNormalBehaviorGrid());
1527 if (position == ContentPosition::End)
1528 return m_columnPositions[lastLine];
1529 if (position == ContentPosition::Start || style().resolvedJustifyContentDistribution(contentAlignmentNormalBehaviorGrid()) == ContentDistribution::Stretch)
1530 return m_columnPositions[0] - borderAndPaddingLogicalLeft() + clientLogicalWidth();
1531 return clientLogicalWidth();
1532}
1533
1534LayoutUnit RenderGrid::gridAreaBreadthForOutOfFlowChild(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction)
1535{
1536 ASSERT(child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1537 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
1538 GridSpan span = GridPositionsResolver::resolveGridPositionsFromStyle(style(), child, direction, autoRepeatCountForDirection(direction));
1539 if (span.isIndefinite())
1540 return isRowAxis ? clientLogicalWidth() : clientLogicalHeight();
1541
1542 unsigned explicitStart = m_grid.explicitGridStart(direction);
1543 int startLine = span.untranslatedStartLine() + explicitStart;
1544 int endLine = span.untranslatedEndLine() + explicitStart;
1545 int lastLine = numTracks(direction, m_grid);
1546 GridPosition startPosition = direction == ForColumns ? child.style().gridItemColumnStart() : child.style().gridItemRowStart();
1547 GridPosition endPosition = direction == ForColumns ? child.style().gridItemColumnEnd() : child.style().gridItemRowEnd();
1548
1549 bool startIsAuto = startPosition.isAuto() || startLine < 0 || startLine > lastLine;
1550 bool endIsAuto = endPosition.isAuto() || endLine < 0 || endLine > lastLine;
1551
1552 if (startIsAuto && endIsAuto)
1553 return isRowAxis ? clientLogicalWidth() : clientLogicalHeight();
1554
1555 LayoutUnit start;
1556 LayoutUnit end;
1557 auto& positions = isRowAxis ? m_columnPositions : m_rowPositions;
1558 auto& outOfFlowItemLine = isRowAxis ? m_outOfFlowItemColumn : m_outOfFlowItemRow;
1559 LayoutUnit borderEdge = isRowAxis ? borderLogicalLeft() : borderBefore();
1560 if (startIsAuto)
1561 start = resolveAutoStartGridPosition(direction) + borderEdge;
1562 else {
1563 outOfFlowItemLine.set(&child, startLine);
1564 start = positions[startLine];
1565 }
1566 if (endIsAuto)
1567 end = resolveAutoEndGridPosition(direction) + borderEdge;
1568 else {
1569 end = positions[endLine];
1570 // These vectors store line positions including gaps, but we shouldn't consider them for the edges of the grid.
1571 std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableSizeForGutters = availableSpaceForGutters(direction);
1572 if (endLine > 0 && endLine < lastLine) {
1573 ASSERT(!m_grid.needsItemsPlacement());
1574 end -= guttersSize(m_grid, direction, endLine - 1, 2, availableSizeForGutters);
1575 end -= isRowAxis ? m_offsetBetweenColumns.distributionOffset : m_offsetBetweenRows.distributionOffset;
1576 }
1577 }
1578 return std::max(end - start, 0_lu);
1579}
1580
1581LayoutUnit RenderGrid::logicalOffsetForOutOfFlowChild(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, LayoutUnit trackBreadth) const
1582{
1583 ASSERT(child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1584 if (hasStaticPositionForChild(child, direction))
1585 return 0_lu;
1586
1587 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
1588 bool isFlowAwareRowAxis = GridLayoutFunctions::flowAwareDirectionForChild(*this, child, direction) == ForColumns;
1589 LayoutUnit childPosition = isFlowAwareRowAxis ? child.logicalLeft() : child.logicalTop();
1590 LayoutUnit gridBorder = isRowAxis ? borderLogicalLeft() : borderBefore();
1591 LayoutUnit childMargin = isRowAxis ? child.marginLogicalLeft(&style()) : child.marginBefore(&style());
1592 LayoutUnit offset = childPosition - gridBorder - childMargin;
1593 if (!isRowAxis || style().isLeftToRightDirection())
1594 return offset;
1595
1596 LayoutUnit childBreadth = isFlowAwareRowAxis ? child.logicalWidth() + child.marginLogicalWidth() : child.logicalHeight() + child.marginLogicalHeight();
1597 return trackBreadth - offset - childBreadth;
1598}
1599
1600void RenderGrid::gridAreaPositionForOutOfFlowChild(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, LayoutUnit& start, LayoutUnit& end) const
1601{
1602 ASSERT(child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1603 ASSERT(GridLayoutFunctions::hasOverridingContainingBlockContentSizeForChild(child, direction));
1604 LayoutUnit trackBreadth = GridLayoutFunctions::overridingContainingBlockContentSizeForChild(child, direction).value();
1605 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
1606 auto& outOfFlowItemLine = isRowAxis ? m_outOfFlowItemColumn : m_outOfFlowItemRow;
1607 start = isRowAxis ? borderLogicalLeft() : borderBefore();
1608 if (auto line = outOfFlowItemLine.get(&child)) {
1609 auto& positions = isRowAxis ? m_columnPositions : m_rowPositions;
1610 start = positions[line.value()];
1611 }
1612 start += logicalOffsetForOutOfFlowChild(child, direction, trackBreadth);
1613 end = start + trackBreadth;
1614}
1615
1616void RenderGrid::gridAreaPositionForInFlowChild(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, LayoutUnit& start, LayoutUnit& end) const
1617{
1618 ASSERT(!child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1619 const GridSpan& span = m_grid.gridItemSpan(child, direction);
1620 // FIXME (lajava): This is a common pattern, why not defining a function like
1621 // positions(direction) ?
1622 auto& positions = direction == ForColumns ? m_columnPositions : m_rowPositions;
1623 start = positions[span.startLine()];
1624 end = positions[span.endLine()];
1625 // The 'positions' vector includes distribution offset (because of content
1626 // alignment) and gutters so we need to subtract them to get the actual
1627 // end position for a given track (this does not have to be done for the
1628 // last track as there are no more positions's elements after it, nor for
1629 // collapsed tracks).
1630 if (span.endLine() < positions.size() - 1
1631 && !(m_grid.hasAutoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction)
1632 && m_grid.isEmptyAutoRepeatTrack(direction, span.endLine()))) {
1633 end -= gridGap(direction) + gridItemOffset(direction);
1634 }
1635}
1636
1637void RenderGrid::gridAreaPositionForChild(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction, LayoutUnit& start, LayoutUnit& end) const
1638{
1639 if (child.isOutOfFlowPositioned())
1640 gridAreaPositionForOutOfFlowChild(child, direction, start, end);
1641 else
1642 gridAreaPositionForInFlowChild(child, direction, start, end);
1643}

1645ContentPosition static resolveContentDistributionFallback(ContentDistribution distribution)
1646{
1647 switch (distribution) {
1648 case ContentDistribution::SpaceBetween:
1649 return ContentPosition::Start;
1650 case ContentDistribution::SpaceAround:
1651 return ContentPosition::Center;
1652 case ContentDistribution::SpaceEvenly:
1653 return ContentPosition::Center;
1654 case ContentDistribution::Stretch:
1655 return ContentPosition::Start;
1656 case ContentDistribution::Default:
1657 return ContentPosition::Normal;
1658 }
1659
1660 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1661 return ContentPosition::Normal;
1662}
1663
1664static void contentDistributionOffset(ContentAlignmentData& offset, const LayoutUnit& availableFreeSpace, ContentPosition& fallbackPosition, ContentDistribution distribution, unsigned numberOfGridTracks)
1665{
1666 if (distribution != ContentDistribution::Default && fallbackPosition == ContentPosition::Normal)
1667 fallbackPosition = resolveContentDistributionFallback(distribution);
1668
1669 // Initialize to an invalid offset.
1670 offset.positionOffset = -1_lu;
1671 offset.distributionOffset = -1_lu;
1672 if (availableFreeSpace <= 0)
1673 return;
1674
1675 LayoutUnit positionOffset;
1676 LayoutUnit distributionOffset;
1677 switch (distribution) {
1678 case ContentDistribution::SpaceBetween:
1679 if (numberOfGridTracks < 2)
1680 return;
1681 distributionOffset = availableFreeSpace / (numberOfGridTracks - 1);
1682 positionOffset = 0_lu;
1683 break;
1684 case ContentDistribution::SpaceAround:
1685 if (numberOfGridTracks < 1)
1686 return;
1687 distributionOffset = availableFreeSpace / numberOfGridTracks;
1688 positionOffset = distributionOffset / 2;
1689 break;
1690 case ContentDistribution::SpaceEvenly:
1691 distributionOffset = availableFreeSpace / (numberOfGridTracks + 1);
1692 positionOffset = distributionOffset;
1693 break;
1694 case ContentDistribution::Stretch:
1695 case ContentDistribution::Default:
1696 return;
1697 default:
1698 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1699 return;
1700 }
1701
1702 offset.positionOffset = positionOffset;
1703 offset.distributionOffset = distributionOffset;
1704}
