1706StyleContentAlignmentData RenderGrid::contentAlignment(GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
1707{
1708 return direction == ForColumns ? style().resolvedJustifyContent(contentAlignmentNormalBehaviorGrid()) : style().resolvedAlignContent(contentAlignmentNormalBehaviorGrid());
1709}
1710
1711void RenderGrid::computeContentPositionAndDistributionOffset(GridTrackSizingDirection direction, const LayoutUnit& availableFreeSpace, unsigned numberOfGridTracks)
1712{
1713 bool isRowAxis = direction == ForColumns;
1714 auto& offset =
1715 isRowAxis ? m_offsetBetweenColumns : m_offsetBetweenRows;
1716 auto contentAlignmentData = contentAlignment(direction);
1717 auto position = contentAlignmentData.position();
1718 // If <content-distribution> value can't be applied, 'position' will become the associated
1719 // <content-position> fallback value.
1720 contentDistributionOffset(offset, availableFreeSpace, position, contentAlignmentData.distribution(), numberOfGridTracks);
1721 if (offset.isValid())
1722 return;
1723
1724 if (availableFreeSpace <= 0 && contentAlignmentData.overflow() == OverflowAlignment::Safe) {
1725 offset.positionOffset = 0_lu;
1726 offset.distributionOffset = 0_lu;
1727 return;
1728 }
1729
1730 LayoutUnit positionOffset;
1731 switch (position) {
1732 case ContentPosition::Left:
1733 ASSERT(isRowAxis);
1734 break;
1735 case ContentPosition::Right:
1736 ASSERT(isRowAxis);
1737 positionOffset = availableFreeSpace;
1738 break;
1739 case ContentPosition::Center:
1740 positionOffset = availableFreeSpace / 2;
1741 break;
1742 case ContentPosition::FlexEnd: // Only used in flex layout, for other layout, it's equivalent to 'end'.
1743 case ContentPosition::End:
1744 if (isRowAxis)
1745 positionOffset = style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? availableFreeSpace : 0_lu;
1746 else
1747 positionOffset = availableFreeSpace;
1748 break;
1749 case ContentPosition::FlexStart: // Only used in flex layout, for other layout, it's equivalent to 'start'.
1750 case ContentPosition::Start:
1751 if (isRowAxis)
1752 positionOffset = style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? 0_lu : availableFreeSpace;
1753 break;
1754 case ContentPosition::Baseline:
1755 case ContentPosition::LastBaseline:
1756 // FIXME: Implement the previous values. For now, we always 'start' align.
1757 // http://webkit.org/b/145566
1758 if (isRowAxis)
1759 positionOffset = style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? 0_lu : availableFreeSpace;
1760 break;
1761 case ContentPosition::Normal:
1762 default:
1763 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1764 return;
1765 }
1766
1767 offset.positionOffset = positionOffset;
1768 offset.distributionOffset = 0_lu;
1769}

1771LayoutUnit RenderGrid::translateOutOfFlowRTLCoordinate(const RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit coordinate) const
1772{
1773 ASSERT(child.isOutOfFlowPositioned());
1774 ASSERT(!style().isLeftToRightDirection());
1775
1776 if (m_outOfFlowItemColumn.get(&child))
1777 return translateRTLCoordinate(coordinate);
1778
1779 return borderLogicalLeft() + borderLogicalRight() + clientLogicalWidth() - coordinate;
1780}
1781
1782LayoutUnit RenderGrid::translateRTLCoordinate(LayoutUnit coordinate) const
1783{
1784 ASSERT(!style().isLeftToRightDirection());
1785
1786 LayoutUnit alignmentOffset = m_columnPositions[0];
1787 LayoutUnit rightGridEdgePosition = m_columnPositions[m_columnPositions.size() - 1];
1788 return rightGridEdgePosition + alignmentOffset - coordinate;
1789}

1791// FIXME: SetLogicalPositionForChild has only one caller, consider its refactoring in the future.
1792void RenderGrid::setLogicalPositionForChild(RenderBox& child) const
1793{
1794 // "In the positioning phase [...] calculations are performed according to the writing mode of the containing block of the box establishing the
1795 // orthogonal flow." However, 'setLogicalLocation' will only take into account the child's writing-mode, so the position may need to be transposed.
1796 LayoutPoint childLocation(logicalOffsetForChild(child, ForColumns), logicalOffsetForChild(child, ForRows));
1797 child.setLogicalLocation(GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, child) ? childLocation.transposedPoint() : childLocation);
1798}
1799
1800void RenderGrid::setLogicalOffsetForChild(RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
1801{
1802 if (!child.isGridItem() && hasStaticPositionForChild(child, direction))
1803 return;
1804 // 'setLogicalLeft' and 'setLogicalTop' only take into account the child's writing-mode, that's why 'flowAwareDirectionForChild' is needed.
1805 if (GridLayoutFunctions::flowAwareDirectionForChild(*this, child, direction) == ForColumns)
1806 child.setLogicalLeft(logicalOffsetForChild(child, direction));
1807 else
1808 child.setLogicalTop(logicalOffsetForChild(child, direction));
1809}
1810
1811LayoutUnit RenderGrid::logicalOffsetForChild(const RenderBox& child, GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
1812{
1813 if (direction == ForRows)
1814 return columnAxisOffsetForChild(child);
1815 LayoutUnit rowAxisOffset = rowAxisOffsetForChild(child);
1816 // We stored m_columnPositions's data ignoring the direction, hence we might need now
1817 // to translate positions from RTL to LTR, as it's more convenient for painting.
1818 if (!style().isLeftToRightDirection())
1819 rowAxisOffset = (child.isOutOfFlowPositioned() ? translateOutOfFlowRTLCoordinate(child, rowAxisOffset) : translateRTLCoordinate(rowAxisOffset)) - (GridLayoutFunctions::isOrthogonalChild(*this, child) ? child.logicalHeight() : child.logicalWidth());
1820 return rowAxisOffset;
1821}

1823unsigned RenderGrid::nonCollapsedTracks(GridTrackSizingDirection direction) const
1824{
1825 auto& tracks = m_trackSizingAlgorithm.tracks(direction);
1826 size_t numberOfTracks = tracks.size();
1827 bool hasCollapsedTracks = m_grid.hasAutoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction);
1828 size_t numberOfCollapsedTracks = hasCollapsedTracks ? m_grid.autoRepeatEmptyTracks(direction)->size() : 0;
1829 return numberOfTracks - numberOfCollapsedTracks;
1830}

1832unsigned RenderGrid::numTracks(GridTrackSizingDirection direction, const Grid& grid) const
1833{
1834 // Due to limitations in our internal representation, we cannot know the number of columns from
1835 // m_grid *if* there is no row (because m_grid would be empty). That's why in that case we need
1836 // to get it from the style. Note that we know for sure that there are't any implicit tracks,
1837 // because not having rows implies that there are no "normal" children (out-of-flow children are
1838 // not stored in m_grid).
1839 ASSERT(!grid.needsItemsPlacement());
1840 if (direction == ForRows)
1841 return grid.numTracks(ForRows);
1842
1843 // FIXME: This still requires knowledge about m_grid internals.
1844 return grid.numTracks(ForRows) ? grid.numTracks(ForColumns) : GridPositionsResolver::explicitGridColumnCount(style(), grid.autoRepeatTracks(ForColumns));
1845}

1851 paintChild(*child, paintInfo, paintOffset, forChild, usePrintRect, PaintAsInlineBlock);

1867bool RenderGrid::hasAutoSizeInColumnAxis(const RenderBox& child) const
1868{
1869 if (child.style().hasAspectRatio()) {
1870 if (isHorizontalWritingMode() == child.isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
1871 // A non-auto inline size means the same for block size (column axis size) because of the aspect ratio.
1872 if (!child.style().logicalWidth().isAuto())
1873 return false;
1874 } else {
1875 const Length& logicalHeight = child.style().logicalHeight();
1876 if (logicalHeight.isFixed() || (logicalHeight.isPercentOrCalculated() && child.percentageLogicalHeightIsResolvable()))
1877 return false;
1878 }
1879 }
1880 return isHorizontalWritingMode() ? child.style().height().isAuto() : child.style().width().isAuto();
1881}
1882
1883bool RenderGrid::hasAutoSizeInRowAxis(const RenderBox& child) const
1884{
1885 if (child.style().hasAspectRatio()) {
1886 if (isHorizontalWritingMode() == child.isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
1887 // A non-auto block size means the same for inline size (row axis size) because of the aspect ratio.
1888 const Length& logicalHeight = child.style().logicalHeight();
1889 if (logicalHeight.isFixed() || (logicalHeight.isPercentOrCalculated() && child.percentageLogicalHeightIsResolvable()))
1890 return false;
1891 } else {
1892 if (!child.style().logicalWidth().isAuto())
1893 return false;
1894 }
1895 }
1896 return isHorizontalWritingMode() ? child.style().width().isAuto() : child.style().height().isAuto();
1897}
